description: Permanently deletes a  ByteMatchSet. You can't delete a ByteMatchSet if it's still used in any Rules or if it still includes any  ByteMatchTuple objects (any filters). If you just want to remove a ByteMatchSet from a Rule, use  UpdateRule. To permanently delete a ByteMatchSet, perform the following steps:

parameters.name: ByteMatchSetId
parameters.description: The ByteMatchSetId of the  ByteMatchSet that you want to delete. ByteMatchSetId is returned by  CreateByteMatchSet and by  ListByteMatchSets.

parameters.name: ChangeToken
parameters.description: The value returned by the most recent call to  GetChangeToken.

nested_items.name: ChangeToken
nested_items.description: The ChangeToken that you used to submit the DeleteByteMatchSet request. You can also use this value to query the status of the request. For more information, see  GetChangeTokenStatus.
